                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12669578" author="noble.paul" created="Mon, 2 Feb 2009 12:04:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;updated to trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12669938" author="shalinmangar" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2009 12:26:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Are there any objections on getting this committed? Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12669962" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2009 14:14:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If there were also a way to specify a different index directory, we could get rid of the new file based method, right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12669996" author="shalinmangar" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2009 15:47:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not entirely. This may help if we reload the core which happens rarely (replication of new configuration). The file based method is necessary in case of out of sync index (requiring a new index directory) but when there is no need to reload the current core and a commit will suffice.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12670000" author="noble.paul" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2009 16:02:21 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;If there were also a way to specify a different index directory, we could get rid of the new file based method, right? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;do you mean having a dataDir as well as the indexDir ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means we will have to call persist from  a handler after changing that. Currently there is no means to change any property while the core is up and running. It is only possible during core creation. We will have to make quite some changes to make this possible&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12670007" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2009 16:32:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, I think I see - index.propertiesis created programmaticallly by SnapPuller... that does change things (I had thought a user would need to create it manually).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12671068" author="shalinmangar" created="Fri, 6 Feb 2009 09:21:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixing issue with absolute paths ending with a &apos;/&apos; character.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12671072" author="shalinmangar" created="Fri, 6 Feb 2009 09:30:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 741490.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Added ability to specify dataDir in solr.xml as well as ability to specify dataDir in CoreAdmin&apos;s core create command.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Noble!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12682988" author="shalinmangar" created="Wed, 18 Mar 2009 11:02:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changes to CoreContainer.persist to save dataDir if specified in solr.xml&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
